c: 46
v: 26
t: "Indeed, We had established them in a way We have not established you ˹Meccans˺. And We gave them hearing, sight, and intellect. But neither their hearing, sight, nor intellect were of any benefit to them whatsoever, since they persisted in denying God’s signs. And ˹so˺ they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"